MMA .m16n8k16 Fragment Layout for Accumulator Matrix C/D with .s32 Type

OVERVIEW
Matrix: C/D (Accumulator)
Dimensions: M=16, N=8, K=16
Data type: .s32
Number of registers per thread: 4 (c0, c1, c2, c3), each holding one .s32 value
Elements per register: 1 (s32 values are NOT packed; one element per 32-bit register)

GRID STRUCTURE
The table uses R\C notation where R = matrix row index, C = matrix column index (0-7).
Columns 0-1 form one group, columns 2-3 form a second group, columns 4-5 form a third group, columns 6-7 form a fourth group.
Each cell shows which thread holds those elements and which register names (c0, c1, c2, c3) map to those column positions.

DETAILED LAYOUT TABLE

Matrix Rows 0-7 (upper half), using registers c0 and c1:

Row 0, Cols 0-1: T0 holds {c0, c1}
Row 0, Cols 2-3: T1 holds {c0, c1}
Row 0, Cols 4-5: T2 holds {c0, c1}
Row 0, Cols 6-7: T3 holds {c0, c1}

Row 1, Cols 0-1: T4 holds {c0, c1}
Row 1, Cols 2-3: T5 holds {c0, c1}
Row 1, Cols 4-5: T6 holds {c0, c1}
Row 1, Cols 6-7: T7 holds {c0, c1}

Row 2 through Row 7 continue the same pattern (indicated by arrows in the figure showing continuation), with threads T8 through T27 filling rows 2-6 in groups of 4 threads per row, and:

Row 7, Cols 0-1: T28 holds {c0, c1}
Row 7, Cols 2-3: T29 holds {c0, c1}
Row 7, Cols 4-5: T30 holds {c0, c1}
Row 7, Cols 6-7: T31 holds {c0, c1}

Matrix Rows 8-15 (lower half), using registers c2 and c3:

Row 8, Cols 0-1: T0 holds {c2, c3}
Row 8, Cols 2-3: T1 holds {c2, c3}
Row 8, Cols 4-5: T2 holds {c2, c3}
Row 8, Cols 6-7: T3 holds {c2, c3}

Row 9, Cols 0-1: T4 holds {c2, c3}
Row 9, Cols 2-3: T5 holds {c2, c3}
Row 9, Cols 4-5: T6 holds {c2, c3}
Row 9, Cols 6-7: T7 holds {c2, c3}

Row 10 through Row 14 continue the same pattern (indicated by arrows), with threads T8 through T27 filling rows 10-14 in groups of 4 threads per row, and:

Row 15, Cols 0-1: T28 holds {c2, c3}
Row 15, Cols 2-3: T29 holds {c2, c3}
Row 15, Cols 4-5: T30 holds {c2, c3}
Row 15, Cols 6-7: T31 holds {c2, c3}

GROUPING PATTERN SUMMARY
Threads T0-T31 each cover 2 columns across all 16 rows.
Each thread holds exactly 4 registers: c0, c1, c2, c3.
Registers c0 and c1 correspond to the upper 8 rows (rows 0-7) of the thread's assigned column pair.
Registers c2 and c3 correspond to the lower 8 rows (rows 8-15) of the thread's assigned column pair.
Within each group of 4 consecutive threads (T0-T3, T4-T7, ..., T28-T31), each thread covers a different pair of columns: thread group offset 0 covers cols 0-1, offset 1 covers cols 2-3, offset 2 covers cols 4-5, offset 3 covers cols 6-7.
Each group of 4 threads covers one matrix row in the upper half and the corresponding row in the lower half.
The row assignment per thread group: T0-T3 cover rows 0 and 8, T4-T7 cover rows 1 and 9, T8-T11 cover rows 2 and 10, T12-T15 cover rows 3 and 11, T16-T19 cover rows 4 and 12, T20-T23 cover rows 5 and 13, T24-T27 cover rows 6 and 14, T28-T31 cover rows 7 and 15.

REGISTER PACKING
Each .s32 element occupies one full 32-bit register. There is no packing of multiple values into a single register. Each of c0, c1, c2, c3 holds exactly one .s32 accumulator value.

